
	<sn><md>## Trade Wind{.text-center}

Trade winds are steady, persistent winds that blow from the subtropical high-pressure belts (around 30° latitude) toward the equatorial low-pressure belt (the doldrums). They are one of the **primary winds** of the Earth’s atmospheric circulation system and play a crucial role in climate, navigation, and ocean currents.

#### Origin of Trade Winds

The origin of trade winds can be explained through the ++Hadley Cell circulation++ and the combined effects of the **Pressure Gradient Force (PGF)** and the **Coriolis force**.

---

#### Mechanism of Trade Wind Circulation (Hadley Cell){.text-center}
* Subtorpical to Equator (**PGF**)
* Airlift
* Diverse toward Pole
* Air Sink due to condensation and heavier weight
* Sink to Subtropical and Cycle Continue
